article.description: — Trey Moss had 20 points in William & Mary's 85-73 victory against Hampton on Saturday.
article.headline: Moss puts up 20, William & Mary downs Hampton 85-73
article.linkText: Moss puts up 20, William & Mary downs Hampton 85-73
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- — Trey Moss had 20 points in William & Mary's 85-73 victory against Hampton on Saturday. Moss was 7 of 13 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Tribe (9-22, 4-14 Coastal Athletic Association). Gabe Dorsey scored 19 points, going 5 of 16 from the floor, including 5 for 15 from 3-point range, and 4 for 6 from the line. Sean Houpt was 5 of 11 shooting (5 for 9 from 3-point range) to finish with 16 points. The victory snapped a nine-game slide for the Tribe. Ja'Von Benson finished with 19 points, nine rebounds and five blocks for the Pirates (8-23, 3-15). Tre Thomas added nine points and six rebounds for Hampton. Jordan Nesbitt also recorded nine points and six assists. Houpt led William & Mary in scoring with 13 points in the first half to help put them up 43-35 at the break. William & Mary pulled away with a 9-0 run in the second half to extend an eight-point lead to 17. They outscored Hampton by four points in the final half, as Dorsey led the way with a team-high 16 second-half points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
